      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ZIPPING SINGH (6) is a capable type and proved too classy last time to win by 0.8 lengths at The Meadows in a handy 34.96 beating Archer Sweet. Recorded one of the quickest times on the card in scoring last start. Expected to be right there at the finish again. MORAINE SARA (2) bolted in last time, scoring by 2.75 lengths in slick time (29.77) to take a Grade 5 in a new PB this course and distance. Should be in this for a long way. PAW GELDOFF (4) turned in a better effort at The Meadows last start, finishing second behind Aunty Faye (30.61) in a Grade 5. Led around the bend before fighting on well and should give a sight. Hard to beat again. MOTOR CITY ROSSI (8) has claims again if he runs up to the latest effort.",
